Comment¶

  1. Heatmap confirms pairplot analysis. The column 'Avg_Credit_Limit' is highly correlated with 'Total_visits_online' and is inversely correlated with 'Total_calls_made'.

  2. The customers who visit online or even make calls seems to visit bank less. This will be useful for improving customer care.

  3. The 'Total_calls_made' is highly inversely related to 'Total_Credit_Cards'. The customers who make calls have less credit cards.

Other group could be customers having more credit limit and more credit cards.

3. Execute K-means clustering use elbow plot and analyse clusters using boxplot (10 marks)¶

In [128]:
from scipy.spatial.distance import cdist
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

clusters=range(1,10)
meanDistortions=[]

for k in clusters:
    model=KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    model.fit(df)
    prediction=model.predict(df)
    meanDistortions.append(sum(np.min(cdist(df, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1)) / df
                           .shape[0])


plt.plot(clusters, meanDistortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average distortion')
plt.title('Selecting k with the Elbow Method')
Out[128]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Selecting k with the Elbow Method')

6. Compare K-means clusters with Hierarchical clusters. (5 marks)¶

K-means clustering and Hierarchical clustering cannot be really compared directly.

If we look at Elbow method for K-means, we can optimized clustering using 2,3 and 4 clusters. Out of these 3 numbers, 3 cluster K-means give better silhouette score.

With hierarchical clustering, we are using 3 different methods (Average, Complete and Ward) for linkage clustering.

Cophenet index(closer to 1, better clustering)

  1. Average Linkage : 0.8977080867389372
  2. Complete Linkage : 0.8599730607972423
  3. Ward Linkage : 0.7415156284827493

Out of which, average linkage has best cophenet index.

To attempt comparing K-means and Hierarchical clustering, I used boxplot using fcluster for Hierarchical clustering.

In this attempt, if we use distance as a measure then sometime, all rows are present in only one cluster. To make comparison better, I have used 'maxclust' as criteria for fcluster. In this case,3 value for 'maxclust' gives best silhouette score.

I am going to compare K-means 3 cluster and hierarchical clustering - Average Linkage with 3 clusters below.

From above comparison, the cluster group to which each row of data belong may be different using Kmeans and Hierarchical clustering. but from boxplot, for each variable, three different groups for each variable are identical using both methods.

Clustering is very subjective. If we have an idea of segments or groups within data using EDA (data analysis), then it is optimal to use K-means. It may be computationally faster than hierarchical clustering.

Hierarchical clustering is a structure that is more informative and interpretable than clusters by k-means.Therefore, it is easier to determine the optimal number of clusters by looking at the dendrogram of a hierarchical clustering than trying to predict this optimal number in advance in case of k-means.

7. Analysis the clusters formed, tell us how is one cluster different from another and answer all the key questions. (10 marks)¶

Problem Statement¶

Project description provides following problem statement.

Objective: To identify different segments in the existing customer based on their spending patterns as well as past interaction with the bank. Key Questions:

  1. How many different segments of customers are there?
  2. How are these segments different from each other?
  3. What are your recommendations to the bank on how to better market to and service these customers?

The 'Avg_Credit_Limit' information is used for determining spending ability.

I am going to use K-means 3 clustering as Hierarchical Average Linkage provides similar clustering.

Different Segments¶

3 Segments

  1. Segment 0 : Average Spending group
  2. Segment 1 : High spending group
  3. Segment 2 : Low spending group

Description of segments:

  1. Customers with Cluster Id 0 have 'Avg_Credit_Limit' value closer to median. The number of credit cards owned by them are also close to 5.
  2. Customers with Cluster Id 1 have high credit limit(high spending ability) and high credit cards.
  3. Customers with Cluster Id 2 have low credit limit.

Those have average spending ability or in middle of range of spending ability - they like to visit bank. The customers with high spending ability always prefer online interaction. They are not interested in any other form of interaction. Where as customers with low spending ability prefer phone interaction but also use online communication/transaction.

Suggestions¶

To increase penetration of customers,

  1. Bank should look at moving customers from Group 2 to group 0 and Group 0 to Group 1. For customers in group 2, bank should call to offer different credit cards and increase their spending ability.
  2. When group 0 customers visit bank, bank should provide promotion offers of credit cards.
  3. For customers in group 1, online promotions will make a difference.

Maximum customers(Group 0 - 386) perfer visiting bank. so bank should have dedicated service department or improve their existing customer service. Bank can also call these customers periodically. It would be worth looking at training this segement for online interaction. Bank can further classify different customer queries.

For recommendation, this data is not enough. It would be helpful if we have some more information like salary/bank balance, amount of money spent and categories on which customers are spending money, queries that are taking more time.
